  "body": "I am trying to run the rpcdaemon in a separate docker container to the erigon node itself, both use a shared data volume on the host, therefore according to the docs I expected I would be able to run the rpc daemon in local mode (not dual)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/cmd/rpcdaemon/README.md#running-locally\r\n\r\n`If you have direct access to Erigon's database folder, you may run the rpcdaemon locally. This may provide faster results.\r\nAfter building, run this command to start the daemon locally:\r\n./build/bin/rpcdaemon --datadir ~/Library/Erigon/ --http.api=eth,debug,net,web3\r\n`\r\n\r\nWhen i run rpc daemon I get this error\r\n```\r\nERROR[07-01|21:16:52.564] Could not connect to DB                  error=\"mdbx_env_open: resource temporarily unavailable, path: /data/erigon/chaindata\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere the docs say that if you provide the --datadir flag, this runs in dual mode, which does not work with docker. \r\n\r\n `Running rpcdaemon in \"Dual-Mode\" (including the --datadir flag) `\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon#rpcdaemon-dual-mode-does-not-work-with-docker-container\r\n",
